TY  - JOUR
AU  - Meyer, Bruce D.
AU  - Rosenbaum, Dan T.
T1  - Welfare, the Earned Income Tax Credit, and the Labor Supply of Single Mothers*
PY  - 2001
Y1  - 2001/08/01
DO  - 10.1162/00335530152466313
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 116
IS  - 3
SP  - 1063
EP  - 1114
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - During 1984–1996, welfare and tax policy were changed to encourage work by single mothers. The Earned Income Tax Credit was expanded, welfare benefits were cut, welfare time limits were added, and welfare cases were terminated. Medicaid for the working poor was expanded, as were training programs and child care. During this same time period there were unprecedented increases in the employment and hours of single mothers. We show that a large share of the increase in work by single mothers can be attributed to the EITC and other tax changes, with smaller shares for welfare benefit cuts, welfare waivers, training programs and child care programs.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1162/00335530152466313
ER  - 



